Migrated from EPA STORET Legacy Database- originally reported by Wisconsin DNR
We monitored the same spot yesterday when it was very cloudy and rainy- today was bright and sunny and I was surprised to get the exact reading of 8.5'.

column1: We saw loons and eagles and our international guests came along today and found the Secchi Disk project really interesting!
Testing a little later in the day with shade on the side of the boat makes a difference.

column2: sunny- calm- shade side of boat
Partly cloudy- light breeze. Previous days have been very stormy. Disk on shade side of boat.
Sunny- light breeze. Previous days very windy. Lots of boat activity. Shade side of boat.
Sunny- light breeze. Lots of boat activity. Shade side of boat.
Mostly sunny- light breeze. Weather has been calm. Very little boat activity.
Sunny- windy- shade side of boat.
Sunny and clear- windy- sunny side of boat due to wind.
Sunny and windy. Two Loons nesting on grass island along with a pair of Geese nesting just a few feet away on same small island!
cloudy- light breeze sunny- light breeze sunny- light breeze
calm- sunny- 25 percent cloud cover- busy boat/ski day
sunny- breezy- 25% cloud cover- no traffic
